# Trivy vulnerability ignore list
# These CVEs exist in npm's bundled dependencies inside the node:24-alpine base image.
# They are NOT in our application code or project dependencies.
# They will be resolved when the Node.js team publishes an updated base image.

# @isaacs/brace-expansion 5.0.0 - DoS via unbounded brace range expansion (in npm's glob)
CVE-2026-25547

# glob 10.4.5 / 11.0.3 - Command Injection via malicious filenames (in npm internals)
CVE-2025-64756

# tar 7.5.1 - Arbitrary file overwrite via unsanitized linkpaths (in npm internals)
CVE-2026-23745

# tar 7.5.1 - Arbitrary file overwrite via Unicode path collision (in npm internals)
CVE-2026-23950

# tar 7.5.1 - Arbitrary file creation via path traversal in hardlink (in npm internals)
CVE-2026-24842

# tar 7.5.x - File overwrite via drive-relative symlink traversal (in npm internals)
CVE-2026-31802

# tar 7.5.7 - Arbitrary file read/write via malicious archive hardlink creation (in npm internals)
CVE-2026-26960

# tar 7.5.7 - Hardlink path traversal via drive-relative linkpath (in npm internals)
CVE-2026-29786

# minimatch 10.1.2 / 9.x / 5.x / 3.x - DoS via specially crafted glob patterns (in npm internals)
CVE-2026-26996

# minimatch 10.1.2 / 9.x / 5.x / 3.x - DoS via unbounded recursive backtracking (in npm internals)
CVE-2026-27903

# minimatch 10.1.2 / 9.x / 5.x / 3.x - DoS via catastrophic backtracking in glob expressions (in npm internals)
CVE-2026-27904
